#. <section class="sutta" id="an8.54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.54:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.54:0.2"
msgid "6. Gotamīvagga"
msgstr "6. Gotamī"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 54. Dīghajāṇusutta → vyagghapajjasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.54:0.3"
msgid "54. Dīghajāṇusutta"
msgstr "54. With Dīghajāṇu"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā koliyesu viharati kakkarapattaṃ nāma koliyānaṃ nigamo."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Koliyans, where they "
"have a town named Kakkarapatta."

msgctxt "an8.54:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho dīghajāṇu koliyaputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho dīghajāṇu "
"koliyaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Dīghajāṇu the Kolyian went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one "
"side, and said to the Buddha:"

#. VAR: kāmabhogino → kāmabhogī (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.54:1.3"
msgid ""
"“mayaṃ, bhante, gihī kāmabhogino puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvasāma, "
"kāsikacandanaṃ paccanubhoma, mālāgandhavilepanaṃ dhārayāma, jātarūparajataṃ "
"sādayāma."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, we are laypeople who enjoy sensual pleasures and living at home with "
"our children. We use sandalwood imported from Kāsi, we wear garlands, "
"perfumes, and makeup, and we accept gold and money."

msgctxt "an8.54:1.4"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ no, bhante, bhagavā amhākaṃ tathā dhammaṃ desetu ye amhākaṃ assu "
"dhammā diṭṭhadhammahitāya diṭṭhadhammasukhāya, samparāyahitāya "
"samparāyasukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"May the Buddha please teach us the Dhamma in a way that leads to our welfare "
"and happiness in this life and in future lives.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārome, byagghapajja, dhammā kulaputtassa diṭṭhadhammahitāya saṃvattanti "
"diṭṭhadhammasukhāya."
msgstr ""
"“Byagghapajja, these four things lead to the welfare and happiness of "
"someone from a good family in this life."

msgctxt "an8.54:2.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

# The context makes it plain what samajivita means. BB has “balanced living”, which to me sound life “work/life balance” or something like that.
#. VAR: samajīvitā → samajīvikatā (bj)
msgctxt "an8.54:2.3"
msgid "Uṭṭhānasampadā, ārakkhasampadā, kalyāṇamittatā, samajīvitā."
msgstr ""
"Accomplishment in initiative, protection, good friendship, and balanced "
"finances."

msgctxt "an8.54:2.4"
msgid "Katamā ca, byagghapajja, uṭṭhānasampadā?"
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in initiative?"

#. VAR: jīvikaṃ → jīvitaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an8.54:2.5"
msgid "Idha, byagghapajja, kulaputto yena kammaṭṭhānena jīvikaṃ kappeti—"
msgstr "It’s when a respectable person earns a living by means such as"

#. VAR: issattena → issatthena (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.54:2.6"
msgid ""
"yadi kasiyā, yadi vaṇijjāya, yadi gorakkhena, yadi issattena, yadi "
"rājaporisena, yadi sippaññatarena—"
msgstr ""
"farming, trade, raising cattle, archery, government service, or one of the "
"professions."

msgctxt "an8.54:2.7"
msgid ""
"tattha dakkho hoti analaso, tatrupāyāya vīmaṃsāya samannāgato, alaṃ kātuṃ "
"alaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"They understand how to go about these things in order to complete and "
"organize the work."

msgctxt "an8.54:2.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajja, uṭṭhānasampadā. (1: 1)"
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in initiative."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.282"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:3.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, byagghapajja, ārakkhasampadā?"
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in protection?"

msgctxt "an8.54:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, byagghapajja, kulaputtassa bhogā honti uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatā "
"bāhābalaparicitā, sedāvakkhittā, dhammikā dhammaladdhā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone from a good family owns legitimate wealth that he has "
"earned by his own efforts and initiative, built up with his own hands, "
"gathered by the sweat of the brow."

msgctxt "an8.54:3.3"
msgid "Te ārakkhena guttiyā sampādeti:"
msgstr "They ensure it is guarded and protected, thinking:"

msgctxt "an8.54:3.4"
msgid ""
"‘kinti me ime bhoge neva rājāno hareyyuṃ, na corā hareyyuṃ, na aggi ḍaheyya, "
"na udakaṃ vaheyya, na appiyā dāyādā hareyyun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘How can I prevent my wealth from being taken by rulers or bandits, consumed "
"by fire, swept away by flood, or taken by unloved heirs?’"

msgctxt "an8.54:3.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajja, ārakkhasampadā. (2: 2)"
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in protection."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:4.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, byagghapajja, kalyāṇamittatā?"
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in good friendship?"

msgctxt "an8.54:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, byagghapajja, kulaputto yasmiṃ gāme vā nigame vā paṭivasati, tattha ye "
"te honti—gahapatī vā gahapatiputtā vā daharā vā vuddhasīlino, vuddhā vā "
"vuddhasīlino, saddhāsampannā, sīlasampannā, cāgasampannā, paññāsampannā—tehi "
"saddhiṃ santiṭṭhati sallapati sākacchaṃ samāpajjati; yathārūpānaṃ "
"saddhāsampannānaṃ saddhāsampadaṃ anusikkhati, yathārūpānaṃ sīlasampannānaṃ "
"sīlasampadaṃ anusikkhati, yathārūpānaṃ cāgasampannānaṃ cāgasampadaṃ "
"anusikkhati, yathārūpānaṃ paññāsampannānaṃ paññāsampadaṃ anusikkhati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a respectable person resides in a town or village. And in that "
"place there are householders or their children who may be young or old, but "
"are mature in conduct, accomplished in faith, ethics, generosity, and "
"wisdom. That person associates with them, converses, and engages in "
"discussion. And they emulate the same kind of accomplishment in faith, "
"ethics, generosity, and wisdom."

msgctxt "an8.54:4.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajja, kalyāṇamittatā. (3: 3)"
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in good friendship."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.283"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:5.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, byagghapajja, samajīvitā?"
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in balanced finances?"

#. VAR: samaṃ jīvikaṃ → samajīvikaṃ (s1-3) | samajīvitaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an8.54:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, byagghapajja, kulaputto āyañca bhogānaṃ viditvā, vayañca bhogānaṃ "
"viditvā, samaṃ jīvikaṃ kappeti nāccogāḷhaṃ nātihīnaṃ: ‘evaṃ me āyo vayaṃ "
"pariyādāya ṭhassati, na ca me vayo āyaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a respectable person, knowing their income and expenditure, "
"balances their finances, being neither too extravagant nor too frugal. They "
"think: ‘In this way my income will exceed my expenditure, not the reverse.’"

#. VAR: onataṃ → oṇataṃ (mr)
#. VAR: unnatan’ti → uṇṇatanti (mr)
msgctxt "an8.54:5.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, byagghapajja, tulādhāro vā tulādhārantevāsī vā tulaṃ paggahetvā "
"jānāti: ‘ettakena vā onataṃ, ettakena vā unnatan’ti;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like an appraiser or their apprentice who, holding up the scales, knows "
"that it’s low by this much or high by this much."

msgctxt "an8.54:5.4"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, byagghapajja, kulaputto āyañca bhogānaṃ viditvā, vayañca "
"bhogānaṃ viditvā, samaṃ jīvikaṃ kappeti nāccogāḷhaṃ nātihīnaṃ: ‘evaṃ me āyo "
"vayaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassati, na ca me vayo āyaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a respectable person, knowing their income and expenditure, "
"balances their finances, being neither too extravagant nor too frugal. They "
"think: ‘In this way my income will exceed my expenditure, not the reverse.’"

# See BB’s note for traditional explanations of this idiom.
#. VAR: jīvikaṃ → jīvitaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: udumbarakhādīvāyaṃ → udumbarakhādikaṃ vāyaṃ (bj, pts1) | udumbarakhādakañcāyaṃ (s1, s2)
msgctxt "an8.54:5.5"
msgid ""
"Sacāyaṃ, byagghapajja, kulaputto appāyo samāno uḷāraṃ jīvikaṃ kappeti, tassa "
"bhavanti vattāro: ‘udumbarakhādīvāyaṃ kulaputto bhoge khādatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"If a respectable person has little income but an opulent life, people will "
"say: ‘This respectable person eats their wealth like a fig-eater!’"

#. VAR: jīvikaṃ → jīvitaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: ajeṭṭhamaraṇaṃvāyaṃ → ajaddhumārikaṃ vāyaṃ (bj, pts1) | addhamārakañcāyaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an8.54:5.6"
msgid ""
"Sace panāyaṃ, byagghapajja, kulaputto mahāyo samāno kasiraṃ jīvikaṃ kappeti, "
"tassa bhavanti vattāro: ‘ajeṭṭhamaraṇaṃvāyaṃ kulaputto marissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"If a respectable person has a large income but a spartan life, people will "
"say: ‘This respectable person is starving themselves to death!’"

msgctxt "an8.54:5.7"
msgid ""
"Yato ca khoyaṃ, byagghapajja, kulaputto āyañca bhogānaṃ viditvā, vayañca "
"bhogānaṃ viditvā, samaṃ jīvikaṃ kappeti nāccogāḷhaṃ nātihīnaṃ: ‘evaṃ me āyo "
"vayaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassati, na ca me vayo āyaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"But a respectable person, knowing their income and expenditure, leads a "
"balanced life, neither too extravagant nor too frugal, thinking: ‘In this "
"way my income will exceed my expenditure, not the reverse.’"

msgctxt "an8.54:5.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajja, samajīvitā."
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in balanced finances."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:6.1"
msgid "Evaṃ samuppannānaṃ, byagghapajja, bhogānaṃ cattāri apāyamukhāni honti—"
msgstr "There are four drains on wealth that has been gathered in this way."

msgctxt "an8.54:6.2"
msgid ""
"itthidhutto, surādhutto, akkhadhutto, pāpamitto pāpasahāyo pāpasampavaṅko."
msgstr ""
"Womanizing, drinking, gambling, and having bad friends, companions, and "
"associates."

msgctxt "an8.54:6.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, byagghapajja, mahato taḷākassa cattāri ceva āyamukhāni, cattāri "
"ca apāyamukhāni."
msgstr "Suppose there was a large reservoir with four inlets and four drains."

msgctxt "an8.54:6.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa puriso yāni ceva āyamukhāni tāni pidaheyya, yāni ca apāyamukhāni tāni "
"vivareyya;"
msgstr "And someone was to open up the drains and close off the inlets,"

msgctxt "an8.54:6.5"
msgid "devo ca na sammā dhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya."
msgstr "and the heavens don’t provide enough rain."

msgctxt "an8.54:6.6"
msgid ""
"Evañhi tassa, byagghapajja, mahato taḷākassa parihāniyeva pāṭikaṅkhā, no "
"vuddhi;"
msgstr "You’d expect that large reservoir to dwindle, not expand."

msgctxt "an8.54:6.7"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ, byagghapajja, evaṃ samuppannānaṃ bhogānaṃ cattāri apāyamukhāni "
"honti—"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are four drains on wealth that has been gathered in "
"this way."

msgctxt "an8.54:6.8"
msgid ""
"itthidhutto, surādhutto, akkhadhutto, pāpamitto pāpasahāyo pāpasampavaṅko."
msgstr ""
"Womanizing, drinking, gambling, and having bad friends, companions, and "
"associates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.284"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ samuppannānaṃ, byagghapajja, bhogānaṃ cattāri āyamukhāni honti—"
msgstr "There are four inlets for wealth that has been gathered in this way."

msgctxt "an8.54:7.2"
msgid ""
"na itthidhutto, na surādhutto, na akkhadhutto, kalyāṇamitto kalyāṇasahāyo "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅko."
msgstr ""
"Not womanizing, drinking, or gambling, and having good friends, companions, "
"and associates."

msgctxt "an8.54:7.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, byagghapajja, mahato taḷākassa cattāri ceva āyamukhāni, cattāri "
"ca apāyamukhāni."
msgstr "Suppose there was a large reservoir with four inlets and four drains."

msgctxt "an8.54:7.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa puriso yāni ceva āyamukhāni tāni vivareyya, yāni ca apāyamukhāni tāni "
"pidaheyya;"
msgstr "And someone was to open up the inlets and close off the drains,"

msgctxt "an8.54:7.5"
msgid "devo ca sammā dhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya."
msgstr "and the heavens provide plenty of rain."

msgctxt "an8.54:7.6"
msgid ""
"Evañhi tassa, byagghapajja, mahato taḷākassa vuddhiyeva pāṭikaṅkhā, no "
"parihāni;"
msgstr "You’d expect that large reservoir to expand, not dwindle."

msgctxt "an8.54:7.7"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, byagghapajja, evaṃ samuppannānaṃ bhogānaṃ cattāri āyamukhāni "
"honti—"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are four inlets for wealth that has been gathered in "
"this way."

msgctxt "an8.54:7.8"
msgid ""
"na itthidhutto, na surādhutto, na akkhadhutto, kalyāṇamitto kalyāṇasahāyo "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅko. (4: 4)"
msgstr ""
"Not womanizing, drinking, or gambling, and having good friends, companions, "
"and associates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:8.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, byagghapajja, cattāro dhammā kulaputtassa diṭṭhadhammahitāya "
"saṃvattanti diṭṭhadhammasukhāya."
msgstr ""
"These are the four things that lead to the welfare and happiness of a "
"respectable person in this life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:9.1"
msgid ""
"Cattārome, byagghapajja, dhammā kulaputtassa samparāyahitāya saṃvattanti "
"samparāyasukhāya."
msgstr ""
"These four things lead to the welfare and happiness of a respectable person "
"in future lives."

msgctxt "an8.54:9.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an8.54:9.3"
msgid "Saddhāsampadā, sīlasampadā, cāgasampadā, paññāsampadā."
msgstr "Accomplishment in faith, ethics, generosity, and wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:10.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, byagghapajja, saddhāsampadā?"
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in faith?"

msgctxt "an8.54:10.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, byagghapajja, kulaputto saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a respectable person has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:"

msgctxt "an8.54:10.3"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "an8.54:10.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajja, saddhāsampadā. (1: 5)"
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in faith."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:11.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, byagghapajja, sīlasampadā?"
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in ethics?"

msgctxt "an8.54:11.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, byagghapajja, kulaputto pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … "
"surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a respectable person doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit "
"sexual misconduct, lie, or consume alcoholic drinks that cause negligence."

msgctxt "an8.54:11.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajja, sīlasampadā. (2: 6)"
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in ethics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:12.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, byagghapajja, cāgasampadā?"
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in generosity?"

msgctxt "an8.54:12.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, byagghapajja, kulaputto vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati "
"muttacāgo payatapāṇi vossaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a respectable person lives at home rid of the stain of stinginess, "
"freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving "
"to give and to share."

msgctxt "an8.54:12.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajja, cāgasampadā. (3: 7)"
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in generosity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.285"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:13.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, byagghapajja, paññāsampadā?"
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in wisdom?"

msgctxt "an8.54:13.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, byagghapajja, kulaputto paññavā hoti, udayatthagāminiyā paññāya "
"samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a respectable person is wise. They have the wisdom of arising and "
"passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending "
"of suffering."

msgctxt "an8.54:13.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajja, paññāsampadā. (4: 8)"
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:14.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, byagghapajja, cattāro dhammā kulaputtassa samparāyahitāya "
"saṃvattanti samparāyasukhāyāti."
msgstr ""
"These are the four things that lead to the welfare and happiness of a "
"respectable person in future lives."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:15.1"
msgid "Uṭṭhātā kammadheyyesu,"
msgstr "They’re enterprising in the workplace,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:15.2"
msgid "appamatto vidhānavā;"
msgstr "diligent in managing things,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: jīvikaṃ → jīvitaṃ (s1, s3, mr)
msgctxt "an8.54:15.3"
msgid "Samaṃ kappeti jīvikaṃ,"
msgstr "they balance their finances,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:15.4"
msgid "sambhataṃ anurakkhati."
msgstr "and preserve their wealth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:16.1"
msgid "Saddho sīlena sampanno,"
msgstr "Faithful, accomplished in ethics,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:16.2"
msgid "vadaññū vītamaccharo;"
msgstr "kind, rid of stinginess,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:16.3"
msgid "Niccaṃ maggaṃ visodheti,"
msgstr "they always purify the path"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:16.4"
msgid "sotthānaṃ samparāyikaṃ."
msgstr "to well-being in lives to come."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:17.1"
msgid "Iccete aṭṭha dhammā ca,"
msgstr "And so these eight qualities"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:17.2"
msgid "saddhassa gharamesino;"
msgstr "of a faithful householder"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:17.3"
msgid "Akkhātā saccanāmena,"
msgstr "are declared by the one who is truly named"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:17.4"
msgid "ubhayattha sukhāvahā."
msgstr "to lead to happiness in both spheres,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an8.54:18.1"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammahitatthāya,"
msgstr "welfare and benefit in this life,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:18.2"
msgid "samparāyasukhāya ca;"
msgstr "and happiness in the future lives."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:18.3"
msgid "Evametaṃ gahaṭṭhānaṃ,"
msgstr "This is how, for a householder,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.54:18.4"
msgid "cāgo puññaṃ pavaḍḍhatī”ti."
msgstr "merit grows by generosity.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
